# BROWSER-core.md - Dev.to Global Rules & Selectors

**CRITICAL RULES (apply to ALL sections):**
- Embed waits at START of each evaluate: `async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); ... }`
- Already-commented check MUST scope to `#comment-trees-container` (unscoped matches nav profile link!)

## Selectors Reference

| Element | Selector |
|---------|----------|
| Notification card | `div.crayons-card.notification` |
| Comment preview | `a.notification__reply-title` |
| Their comment link | `a[href*="/comment/"]` (NOT containing "/{{handle}}/") |
| Already replied badge | HTML contains `>Replied<` |
| Reply button | `button` with innerText "Reply" |
| Reply textarea | `textarea[placeholder="Reply..."]` |
| Submit button | `button` with innerText "Submit" |
| Comment section | `#comments` |
| Comment textarea | `textarea#text-area` |
| Already commented | `#comment-trees-container a[href*="/{{handle}}"]` (length > 0) |
| Reaction drawer | `button[aria-label="reaction-drawer-trigger"]` |
| Like button | `button[aria-label="Like"]` (aria-pressed="true" = liked) |
| Unicorn button | `button[aria-label="Unicorn"]` (aria-pressed="true" = reacted) |
| Follow tag btn | `button.c-btn.c-btn--primary` (text "Follow") |
| Following tag btn | `button.crayons-btn.crayons-btn--outlined` (text "Following") |

## SS 6: Recovery Rules

- **Browser timeout** -> close tab, reopen URL, retry once. If fails -> `exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/open -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"url":"URL"}'` (NOT start!), wait 3s, retry. Still fails -> skip browser tasks.
- **Do not kill Chrome** — use the `/close` endpoint instead.
- **Typing fails** -> use evaluate with `textarea.value = text` + dispatchEvent. Still fails -> skip, retry next heartbeat.
- **"matched N elements" error** -> selector too broad, use narrower selector.
- If evaluate returns unexpected -> check URL, re-navigate if wrong page
- If retry fails -> skip action, log Type="Error", move to next task.
